01/20/86  read_mail request:  switch_off, swf

Syntax:  swf switch_name {message_specifiers}


Function:  turns off a specified switch for each selected message.


Arguments:
switch_name
   currently must be the keyword "seen". The seen switch is on for a
   message that has been printed previously by the print request.
   Turning off a message's seen switch includes it in the value of
   the "unseen" message specifier.
message_specifiers
   identifies messages for which the switch is to be turned off. If no
   message_specifiers and no selection_args are specified, the current
   message is assumed.  For more information on message specifiers,
   type:
         help message_specifiers.gi


Access required:
The user requires "d" extended access to the mailbox.
